giveaspecialstatustothehunterwhoknowsit.Languagethen
becomesnotaninstrumentofcommunicationbutofexclusion,
actingasacodeandabarrier.Thosewhofeelnowadaysthey
shouldsayÑpuddingÄinsteadofÑsweetÄ,ÑsetteeÄinsteadofÑsofaÄ,
manifestasimilarawarenessthattheiruseoflanguagemay
betrayalowsocialclassorignoranceofacceptedform.Inthe
medievalhunt,theinitiatedareunitedbytheirspecialuseof
language,theuninitiatedexcludedbyit.Asweshallseelater
inaliterarycontext,huntingistaughtandlearntasasystem
ofpreciselanguage.Wordsoperateasasemi-magicalkeyto
knowledge;toknowthewordistoapprehendthemeaningand
natureoftheobjectoractivityitdenotes.


